item.title: PAying 50$ for help
item.dc:creator: @robocz033 robocz033
item.description:
@robocz033 wrote:

192.168.1.(enter the last part here)

to find it in xp, go to control panel -> i think its network
and in there you should be your connections, right click the active one (should be local area connection) and select properties, then it should tell you your internal ip.

in vista, just hover your mouse over the network icon in the system tray. if it isnt there, go to start -> control panel -> network and sharing center -> view status and then in the window that pops up click details. its listed as IPv4 address.
